 HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukenshindono69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kenshindono69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/01 12:59:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3618.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ok, whats this faction thing</span><hr size=1> I need to know how this faction with Seru and Katta works out, ive been doing a lot of quests in Katta recently and hanging around there, when i went to seru a little bit back i was dubious to most people there, the next quest i did in Katta i noticed i lost seru faction, whats going on? are these 2 states at war? they both seem like 'good' cities, whats the story here? If they are at war i dont know which to side with, i like Katta better, but Serus has more guild stuff for me. What should a paladin of Erollisi allign himself with, and how does the faction work here?<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzyphyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/01 2:15:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3618.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok, whats this faction thing</span><hr size=1> The 2 cities are the descendants of two opposing/warring faction of the old Combine Empire. They hate each other with a passion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaphyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/01 10:56:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3618.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Ya, both warring cities....Hate each other.  Seru hates evil races....badly.  (Almost ally in gnome form, still way scowl in Dark elf) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tamaraevening>Tamara Evening</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/01 11:50:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3618.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> The old Comine Empire ran the length and bredth of Norrath, a vast community from every section in the realm. At least every 'good' community. As with all things of this size, eventually there grew divisions. One faction believing that they were more pious than the other. The two main faction at work here were the Loyalists and what came to be known as the inquisition.<br>It is rumoured that the divisions finally became too great when those loyal to the Empire wished to welcome the 'Dark Races' into the ranks, provided of course they renouncse their dark ways and work for the good of Norrath. Those loyal to the Seru and his Inquisition revolted over this and the resulting fight tore the once peaceful Empire in two.<br>Realising there was nothing further they could do, those loyal to the Empire gathered the most powerful magics available at that time and more powerful than any since and transported themselves as a whole to the small moon of Luclin.<br>The Inquisition also had these powerful magics and quickly left Norrath in persuit of those who had 'destroyed the Empire with the foul notion of including those who followed the dark path'.<br>On arrival they each built their cities and fortifications; The Inquisition built Seru in the half of the moon forever bathed in the light (and surrounded by the darkest of creatures) while The Loyalists built Katta on the other (darkened) side of Luclin where they struggle against the evil that surrounds them.<br><br>Who is right? As with all tales there are at least two sides, a Rogues place is not to determine who is right or who is wrong, no. We watch from the shadows and hear the tales that both sides will tell. I can say for myself those that would ally themselves with the undead are no friend to me.<br><br>Tamara <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3616.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3620.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3618.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3618.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3618.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3618.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTo